Read allele frequencies from a tab\-delimited file containing
the columns: CHROM\(rstPOS\(rstREF,ALT\(rstAF. The file can be compressed with
\fBbgzip\fP and indexed with tabix \-s1 \-b2 \-e2.  Sites which are not present in
the \fIFILE\fP or have different reference or alternate allele will be skipped.
Note that such a file can be easily created from a VCF using:
.RE
.sp
.if n .RS 4
